column5: Finally managed a decent walleye last night on Buckhorn: 24" and thick, I estimate about 3 1/2 to 4 lbs.  Please excuse the poor photography, I was alone and only had my Blackberry with me.     It sure beats the three I've caught under the slot so far. Now if I could just get one in the slot for dinner...
He'll be crying in his cornflakes over that one Jer.
